<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: auto auto auto auto;
  grid-template-rows: 200px 100px;
  grid-gap: 50px;
  background-color: #2196F3;
  padding: 10px;
}

.grid-container > div {
  background-color: cyan;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 20px 0;
  font-size: 30px;
}
body {
  background-color: orange;
}

@media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {
  body {
    background-color: blue;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>The grid-template-rows Property Page 3</h1>

<p>Use the <em>grid-template-rows</em> property to define the size of the rows in a grid layout.</p>
<p>The first row in this grid is 100px high, and the second row is 300px high:</p>

<div class="grid-container">
  <div class="item1">1</div>
  <div class="item2">2</div>
  <div class="item3">3</div>  
  <div class="item4">4</div>
  <div class="item5">5</div>
  <div class="item6">6</div>
  <div class="item7">7</div>
  <div class="item8">8</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>